title: Grateful Dead Live at Veterans' Memorial Coliseum on 1983-04-23
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi DR-2 > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > R8Brain > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 04/2012
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Finiculi Finicula, Candyman, Minglewood Blues, Tennessee Jed, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Peggy-O, Far From Me, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E:One More Saturday Night-> E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Best sound for my taste Great show, very good sound. I like this the best out of the aud sources. Some might prefer Sir Micks version of Jeff's recording. I like the warmth of this pull better.
Nice! The long and jammy Space~>OtherOne~>Wharf Rat segue here is top notch, and my ears favored this aud pull the most, although the Wise/Clugston/Miller and chasingwila pulls are very good, too!

Awesome show - Excellent recording After sampling every source for this show settled on this pull from Joe Morrone.

It has the combination of warmth and clarity of vocals/instruments that I look for. Nicely balanced. Thanks Joe!

As for the show, there are smoking versions of Minglewood, LLS, and TMNS. Peggy-O is beautiful. So many great Peggies in '83. candyman is a treat and even 

Scarlet > Fire is the headline jam but Space > The Other One is the secret sauce on this night. A haunting Wharf Rat followed by an energizer Stones > NFA and a Brokedown Palace encore make this this my favorite show of the year.

Long Live the LMA!
